overall_summary: Discussion centered on the AI16Z→elizaOS token migration (portal live, 1:6 ratio, 90-day window) and user support for wallet/exchange edge cases. Secondary themes included a containerized headless-Chrome WebGL→RTMP streaming capability and business developments involving X account recovery and Coinbase listing conversations.
key_facts: The AI16Z to elizaOS migration portal was reported as launched on November 6 with a 90-day migration window ending February 4th, 2024.
The conversion ratio communicated in Discord was 1 AI16Z token to 6 elizaOS tokens.
Shaw stated that unclaimed elizaOS tokens after the deadline will not be burned and users can create a support ticket on Discord.
Users reported that after migrating, elizaOS may not appear in Phantom until it is manually enabled/added in token visibility settings.
Jin reported implementing headless Chrome with GPU support to stream WebGL applications to RTMP endpoints from a Docker container.
In the partners channel, Shaw stated a deal is nearly finalized with X to recover accounts via a backdated enterprise license, with an expected timeline of 1–2 weeks.
In the partners channel, Shaw stated there were positive discussions with Coinbase about a potential listing, facilitated by a connection named Gaia.
The Daily Report for 2025-11-07 stated the GitHub repository elizaOS/eliza had 0 new pull requests, 0 merged PRs, 0 new issues, and 0 active contributors that day.
A core release version 1.6.4 was announced in Discord on 2025-11-05.
A security concern was raised that the api/system/env/local endpoint is accessible in development mode.

overall_focus.claim: No GitHub activity was reported for elizaOS/eliza on 2025-11-07; the broader week/month reports emphasize security (entity-level RLS), runtime enhancements, and planned performance features (parallel actions/background tasks).

discord_updates.summary: Users focused on AI16Z→elizaOS migration mechanics (1:6 ratio, 90-day window), wallet troubleshooting (Phantom token visibility), exchange swap timing (temporary balance disappearance), and requests for an official cross-chain contract-address list due to scam concerns.

Jin described a Dockerized headless-Chrome GPU setup for streaming interactive WebGL to RTMP endpoints with live chat integration, with follow-on plans for multiple avatars/shows; additional feedback noted confusion around framework IDs when creating groups and triggering agent posts.

Shaw attributed earlier migration delays to Base LP provider issues; the channel also surfaced business updates (X enterprise license negotiations for account recovery; Coinbase listing discussions) and clarified that unclaimed tokens will be handled via support tickets rather than burns.

user_feedback.feedback_summary: Multiple users requested a comprehensive migration guide with step-by-step instructions and screenshots for common wallets (e.g., Phantom, Solflare).
Users requested a centralized, official source of truth for elizaOS contract addresses across chains to reduce confusion and scam risk.
Users asked for clearer exchange-by-exchange migration timelines due to tokens temporarily disappearing from exchange wallets during swap implementation.
Feature requests included adding staking for elizaOS tokens and implementing EVM-to-EVM bridging (Base/BSC/ETH).
A security concern was raised about api/system/env/local being accessible in development mode by default.

strategic_insights.theme: Migration UX and trust surface area
strategic_insights.insight: Migration-related confusion clustered around exchange swap timing, wallet token visibility, and unofficial contract addresses shared by users. A single canonical contract-address registry and an exchange status tracker are repeatedly requested in-chat.
implications_or_questions: Should the team publish a single signed/verified contract-address page and pin it across announcements and the portal?
Should there be an exchange status dashboard to reduce repetitive support load during the 90-day window?

strategic_insights.insight: The headless-Chrome GPU WebGL→RTMP container is discussed as a reliable 24/7 approach and explicitly floated as an Eliza Cloud feature. This could become a packaged offering if productized with documentation and deployment templates.
implications_or_questions: What minimum interface and deployment target (Cloud/AWS) would make this a supported product feature?
Does this align with near-term roadmap relative to other Cloud SDK priorities (e.g., login with cloud)?

strategic_insights.insight: Partners chat included ongoing negotiations with X for account recovery and Coinbase listing discussions. These items may require coordinated messaging to prevent inconsistent community expectations while outcomes are pending.
implications_or_questions: What comms policy should be used for listing-related discussions to avoid premature market speculation?

market_analysis.observation: Users discussed market volatility (40% up followed by 20% down) during the migration period.
market_analysis.relevance: Price movement discussion can increase support load and migration urgency questions.

market_analysis.observation: Some users reported arbitrage opportunities during migration/exchange swap timing differences.
market_analysis.relevance: Cross-venue swap delays can create temporary price dislocations and user confusion about balances.

market_analysis.observation: A potential Coinbase listing was discussed in the partners channel.
market_analysis.relevance: Listing discussions are a market attention vector and may impact communications strategy during migration.
